  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Dexmedetomidine is a new, highly selective and potent alpha2-adrenoreceptor agonist
      registered for sedation of patients in intensive care units. Although the pharmacokinetics of
      dexmedetomidine have been studied previously also in an ICU setting, there is no information
      on the pharmacokinetics of long-lasting (&gt;48 hours) dexmedetomidine infusions in humans.

      The aim of this study is to study the pharmacokinetics of long-lasting dexmedetomidine
      infusions in ICU patients using the population pharmacokinetics approach.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
